text: Assume you are given a tiny 4-element, fully-associative cache that uses LRU replacement. The cache stores single byte values (i.e., a line is a single byte). If the cache is empty at the beginning of execution, how many misses will the following string of accesses produce? A,D,D,D,A,A,E,C,C,B,B,C,D,E,B,D,B,G,D,D integer misses @ Save & Grade Single attempt Additional attempts available with new variants @
